    Data: Accession numbers and metadata of 97 E. coli genomes from Malawi from Musciha et al

    btESBL_ecoli_musicha_metadata.Rd

    Metadata of a collection of 97 E. coli genomes selected for temporal diversity and diversity in antibiogram Taken from Musicha et al 2017 For full details see original Musicha publication https://doi.org/10.1093/jac/dkx058

    btESBL_ecoli_musicha_metadata

    Format

    An object of class spec_tbl_df (inherits from tbl_df, tbl, data.frame) with 97 rows and 10 columns.

    Details

    The phylogroup and ST here were determined for this study and were not provided in the original metadata; the popPUNK cluster assignemt uses the Horesh database

    #'

    lane

    Unique sample-sequencing run ID

    ID

    Unmique sample ID

    Year

    Year of sample collection

    Sample_type

    Type of clincial sample from which isolate originates

    Age_group

    Age of patient from which sample orignated

    Organism

    Organism

    ST

    Multlocus sequence type as determined by ARIBA

    phylogroup

    Phylogroup following Clermon scheme with in silico PCR

    Cluster

    PopPUNK cluster assignment using the Horesh E. coli database

    Accession

    NCBI Accession number
